In Engliſh thus, Make no Societies nor Coventicles without my Licenſe: Aſſemblies of this kind, as in other Governments they are hurtful, ſo in Monarchies they are exceeding dangerous. Agreable hereto is that of Mecenas in Dio, who pronounceth, 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . That is in Engliſh, Combinations, and Aſſemblies, and Aſſociations, are things that do not very well conſiſt with a Monarchy.
